<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<title>Cyber Threats</title>
<link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">

<style>
.details {
display: none;
background: white;
color: black;
padding: 20px;
margin: 20px auto;
width: 60%;
border-radius: 10px;
}

.details img {
width: 100%;
border-radius: 10px;
margin-top: 10px;
}
</style>

</head>
<body>

<h1>⚠️ Cyber Threats</h1>

<div class="container">

<div class="card" onclick="showDetails('phishing')">
<h2>🎣 Phishing</h2>
<p>Click to learn</p>
</div>

<div class="card" onclick="showDetails('malware')">
<h2>💻 Malware</h2>
<p>Click to learn</p>
</div>

<div class="card" onclick="showDetails('ransomware')">
<h2>🔒 Ransomware</h2>
<p>Click to learn</p>
</div>

</div>

<!-- DETAILS SECTION -->

<div id="phishing" class="details">
<h2>🎣 Phishing Attack</h2>
<img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1550751827-4bd374c3f58b">
<p>Phishing is a cyber attack where fake emails or websites trick users into giving personal information.</p>
<p><b>Example:</b> “Your bank account is blocked. Click here.”</p>
<p><b>Tip:</b> Always check URL before entering details.</p>
</div>

<div id="malware" class="details">
<h2>💻 Malware</h2>
<img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1603791440384-56cd371ee9a7">
<p>Malware is harmful software that damages your system.</p>
<p><b>Example:</b> Installing unknown apps.</p>
<p><b>Tip:</b> Use antivirus software.</p>
</div>

<div id="ransomware" class="details">
<h2>🔒 Ransomware</h2>
<img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1526378722484-bd91ca387e72">
<p>Ransomware locks your files and asks for money.</p>
<p><b>Example:</b> “Pay ₹5000 to unlock data.”</p>
<p><b>Tip:</b> Keep backups.</p>
</div>

<script>
function showDetails(id) {

let all = document.querySelectorAll('.details');
all.forEach(div => div.style.display = 'none');

document.getElementById(id).style.display = 'block';
}
</script>

</body>
</html>
